@NODE NODE_INTR "Introduction"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Introduction@{UB}

I written this program because no freeware program on Aminet converts a
text file in "One Line" only!.

WHY DO THIS??
So, this program is useful when you want to import a text in a DTP or WP program
and you want to put the text in a number of columns greater or different from
the original text.

In that case you have to go at the end-line, "DEL" last character and
(not always) press "SPACE", for all the "end-line" of the text.
OneLine do that for you and converts at one time CR,LF,TAB & dblSPACES!!


The most important changes in this version are: usage of @{"MUI" link NODE_MUI},
a totally rewritten @{"conversion's routines" link NODE_CONVER} and a GUI for @{"GhostScript 8.50" link NODE_GHOST}
(experimental version yet);

also have many others new @{"features" link NODE_FEAT}.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_REQUIR "System requirements"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Requirements@{UB}

* Any Amiga with at least OS 3.1 and some Mb of RAM (!) especially if you want
  to convert/save big files. (see @{" History " link NODE_HIST} too)
* @{"MUI" link NODE_MUI} 3.8+ with the default Classes
* @{"NList.mcc" link NODE_MUI}         v.19+  (included)  NList Open Source Team, (Gilles Masson)
* @{"NListView.mcc" link NODE_MUI}     v.19+  (included)  NList Open Source Team, (Gilles Masson)
* @{"ImageButton.mcc" link NODE_MUI}   v.11+  (included)  from Maik Schreiber
* @{"HotkeyString.mcc" link NODE_MUI}  v.19+  (included)  from Allan Odgaard
* @{"NumericButton.mui" link NODE_MUI} v.19+  (in MUI38usr.lha) di Stefan Stuntz


and optionally, if you want to show the ASCII files without OneLine's internal viewer
(MUI/NList  o  CON:):

* Multiview, EditPad, CygnuED:

  Multiview  in  "SYS:Utilities/" directory
  EditPad    in  "SYS:Tools/"     directory
  CygnusED   in  "SYS:C/"         directory
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_INST "Installation"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Installation@{UB}
You can install OneLine1.4 manually or with the standard installer Commodore.


@{B}Manually@{UB}
type in shell:

Lha -x x OneLine_MUI.lha RAM:
cd RAM:OneLine14
Copy OneLine ../your_path/
Copy OneLine.info ../your_path/
Copy mui/#? MUI:libs/mui/
Copy catalogs/<your_language_dir>/oneline.catalog Locale:catalogs/<your_language_dir>/
Copy Docs/OneLine.guide HELP:

NOTE:
libraries and classes names are CASE-SENSITIVE


@{B}Installer@{UB}
simply double-click the icon and follow the instuctions.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_FEAT "Features"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Features@{UB}

* FREEWARE. No requesters and no expiry date;

* Detect and elaborate all ASCII codes, and especially: @{"CR" link NODE_CRLF},
  @{"LF" link NODE_CRLF}, @{"TAB" link NODE_TAB}, @{"paragraphs" link NODE_PAR}, @{"unprintable characters" link NODE_UNPRINT}, @{"multiples spaces" link NODE_MULTISPC},
  @{"standard sequences" link NODE_STDSEQ} and @{"strange sequences" link NODE_STRANGE} of comma-spaces-other mixed
  characters;

* Multiple @{"Find / Replace" link NODE_FINDREP} function;

* @{"GhostScript GUI" link NODE_GHOST} to handle Adobe PortableDocumentFormat«
  and PostScript« (.PDF .PS);

* Show and save results of the conversion;

* Shortcuts for all the functions;

* Uses various viewers:
  Multiview, EditPad, CygnusED, OneLine 1 (with CON:) and OneLine 2 (with MUI);

* Show the files by double-clicking on entry in the listview;
  using Multiview as viewer (that uses datatypes) you can also show images and other;

* (very!) Simple @{"print" link NODE_PRINT} ASCII file;

* (This) HELP on line;

* MUI-GUI;
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_SHELL "Shell Usage"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Shell usage@{UB}

Sorry, but at the moment, there isn't a Shell version of OneLine.
Maybe, i can compile a Shell version later and if i will receive some requests.

However you can start OneLine1.4 from shell typing:

2.Ram Disk:> stack 25000
2.Ram Disk:> ..<your path>/OneLine
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_WB "Workbench usage"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Workbench usage@{UB}

Simply doubleclick on the icon.

OneLine 1.4 don't uses the Tooltypes: you can select and save all your preferences
in the "Prefs" section.

Each OneLine's gadget has the bubble-help, see them too!

Like others MUI programs also OneLine needs more memory for stack, so you must
set the stack size to 25 Kb at least:
lower values could crash the program or the entire system.

OneLine checks the stack size at start and if isn't enough,
will increase it automatically.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_USAGE "Usage"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Usage@{UB}


In order, in main window you can find:

@{" Info       " link NODE_ME} logo        Info about program and author
@{" About MUI  " link NODE_MUI} logo        Info about MUI
@{" List-files " link NODE_LIST} listview    Listview with the name of the files to convert
Text field with various messages sent from OneLine
@{" Add        " link NODE_ADD} button      Add files to listview
@{" Clear      " link NODE_CLEAR} button      Clear the listview
@{" Erase      " link NODE_ERASE} button      Erase a/some files from the listview
@{" Copy       " link NODE_COPY} button      Copy files
@{" Rename     " link NODE_RENAME} button      Rename files
@{" Delete     " link NODE_DELETE} button      Delete files
@{" Print      " link NODE_PRINT} button      Print files
@{" Go!        " link NODE_GO} button      Start conversion



On "Prefs" tab you can find the following gadgets:

@{" Find/Repl  " link NODE_FINDREP} checkmark    Find and replace characters
@{" OneLine    " link NODE_CRLF} checkmark    Converts to "oneline" only
@{" Tabs       " link NODE_TAB} checkmark    Erases Tabs
@{" Seq        " link NODE_STRANGE} checkmark    Check for strange sequences
@{" Auto Seq   " link NODE_AUTOSEQ} checkmark    Auto-correect strange sequences
@{" Double     " link NODE_DOUBLE} checkmark    Check for the chrs like <>  ""  `'
@{" Multi Spc  " link NODE_MULTISPC} checkmark    Erases multiple spaces
@{" Leave Č    " link NODE_PAR} checkmark    Leave the paragraph's division
@{" Chrs Errs  " link NODE_ERR} checkmark    Check for comma-chrs like errors
@{" Std Seq    " link NODE_STDSEQ} checkmark    Check for standard sequences
@{" Format     " link NODE_FORMAT} checkmark    Format the text with n columns
@{" UnPrint    " link NODE_UNPRINT} checkmark    Erases unprintables chrs
@{" AutoView   " link NODE_AUTOVIEW} checkmark    Auto-view file at end
@{" Stats      " link NODE_STATS} checkmark    Shows statistics on conversion
@{" Save Res   " link NODE_SELECT} checkmark    Select lines
@{" Delay      " link NODE_DELAY} checkmark    Delay between files
@{" UseBreak   " link NODE_USEBREAK} checkmark    Check for CTRL-C
@{" Italiano   " link NODE_ITA} checkmark    Check some chrs

@{" Viewer      " link NODE_VIEW} cycle    Select viewer
@{" columns     " link NODE_FILELUN} num-button    Select number of columns
@{" OS Type     " link NODE_TARGET} cycle    Select target OS
@{" GhostScript " link NODE_GHOST} checkmark    GhostScript 8.50 GUI / Option

@{" Load    " link NODE_LOADSAVE} button    Load preferences
@{" Save    " link NODE_LOADSAVE} button    Save preferences
@{" Default " link NODE_DEFAULT} button    Default preferences


By clicking on @{" Find/Repl " link NODE_FINDREP} or @{" GhostScript 8.50 " link NODE_GHOST} OneLine opens
a window with others options.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_CONVER "Routines"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Routines of conversion@{UB}

OneLine in this version uses another type of conversion:
now do more scans, depending from the options, on source file loaded in RAM.
This means that the total conversion time change if you deactivate one
or more options.

The most time expensive options are "UseBreak" and "Find/Repl".


NOTE: If in the text there're some TABS, the shown text seems to be not
      formatted: this is because the TABS is 1 character too, like others,
      but take up more space... isn't a bug!
      You could use "Erase TAB" option to remove this "problem"
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_FINDREP "Find and replace"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Find and replace@{UB}

This option performs a multiple find/replace function:
OneLine, for all the "Find/Repl" rows, search for the string in "find" column
and, if found, replace it with the string in the respective "replace" column.


This line:
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
Find:         Replace:
Home          work
F             f
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}

will change all "Home" occurrencies with the string "work"
and all "F" occurrencies with "f".


If you want to substitute a single char you can write his ASCII code after
the string $:0 like this ASCII_code:

this line:
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
Find:         Replace:
$:027         C
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}
will change all ESC (Escape  -  ASCII 27) with the character "C"



Until now you can insert single ASCII codes only in "find" field, not in
"replace" field.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_CRLF "CR and LF"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}CR and LF@{UB}

This option will erase the characters CR and/or LF, that is "new line".
It's the main function of OneLine!

The resulting text will be arranged on one line, so, by showing it with/in
a program that don't performs a formatting, you will see one line only;

as well, if you save the text with the MS-DOS or MAC option, it can be showed
in APPARENTLY faulty way:
i.e. you could see a lack of lines.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_TAB "Tabs"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Tabs@{UB}

This option will detect and convert to SPACE the TAB chars
(ASCII - 9).
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_STRANGE "Stranges sequences"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Stranges sequences@{UB}

This option will detect the sequences of comma/chrs without any sense.

I.e.
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
"This is a test.,."!.,of this function"
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}
will be
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
"This is a test, of this function"
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}

The seqeunce ", " must be typed by you.

See the @{"AutoSeq" link NODE_AUTOSEQ} option too
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_AUTOSEQ "Automatic sequences parsing"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Automatic sequences parsing@{UB}

If OneLine find a "@{"strange sequence" link NODE_STRANGE}" with this
option OneLine automatically will substitute all them with a SPACE.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_DOUBLE "Double"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Double@{UB}

This option "try" to detect and parse the doubles characters
(open / close) like () <> {}.

I.e.
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
This is an " example  "of the< function >.
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}
will be
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
This is an "example" of the <function>.
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_MULTISPC "Multiples spaces"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Multiples spaces@{UB}

This option detects and removes the consecutive spaces:

I.e.
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
"Remove  now,      consecutives     spaces"
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}
will be
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
"Remove now, consecutives spaces"
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_PAR "Paragraphs"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Paragraphs@{UB}

This option preserves the paragraph's separations.

I.e. the text:
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
This is an
example of
the function

that preserve
the paragraph's

separations
in the text
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}

without "Paragraph" option will be:
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
This is an example of the function that preserve the paragraph's separations in the text
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}

instead with the "Paragraph" option:
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
This is an example of the function

that preserve the paragraph's

separations in the text
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_ERR "Errors"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Errors@{UB}

With this option OneLine:

1. will erase various sequences like: :^ #& _^ &: etc.

2. will toggle on/off the @{"Standard sequence" link NODE_STDSEQ} e @{"italiano" link NODE_ITA} option
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_STDSEQ "Standard sequences"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Standard sequences@{UB}

This option will detect the sequences, like web-links, and leave them intact:

I.e.
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
"http://www.amiga.com/"
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}
without this option will be:
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
"http: www. amiga. com/"
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_FORMAT "Format text"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Format text@{UB}

If this option is active, at the end of conversion, OneLine will format the text to
the number of columns specified in the "columns" gadget:

If columns = 4 the text:
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
This is a test
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}
will be
@{LINDENT 6}@{B}
This
is a
test
@{UB}@{LINDENT 3}

This option erase the space at begin of line, if found.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_UNPRINT "Unprintables characters"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Unprintables characters@{UB}

This option will erase the characters unprintable like the ASCII CODE < 9.

Note that will erase the characters like FormFeed etc. that could be
useful to print the pages.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_AUTOVIEW "Automatic view"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Automatic view@{UB}

At the end of conversion OneLine automatically show the files
with the viewer selected in "viewer:" option.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_STATS "Statistics"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Statistics@{UB}

With this option OneLine shows a list with the statistics of the conversion,
the input file, the output file and the time employed.

OneLine will save the statistics made, on the file "RAM:OL_Results.txt" too.

The file "RAM:OL_Results.txt" is open with "append" mode therefore the
following results are added at the end of file if it's already present.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_SELECT "Select lines"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Select lines@{UB}

With this option you can select the lines to convert: OneLine will convert these
lines only; the rest will be equal to the original.

Will be open a requester.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_DELAY "Delay"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Delay@{UB}

If you load more than one file in listview with this option OneLine waits
for your input between the files:

without this you can't read any page of statistics.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_USEBREAK "Use break"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Use break@{UB}

This option force OneLine to check for a user break.

Note that this option is very time expensive:
if you disable it you will have visible speed improvement.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_ITA "Italian characters"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Italian characters@{UB}

This option change the sequences like <e'> <o'> to <Ķ> <“>:
it's useful for texts with accented characters like italian or french texts.

For others languages i suggest to uncheck this option.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_GHOST "GhostScript 8.50 section"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}GhostScript 8.50  GUI - section@{UB}

This is a GUI for the program AFPL Ghostscript 8.50.

OneLine search for standard executable path "GS850:bin/gs".
At present isn't possible to insert another path.

If you are using a older version of Ghostscript the executable
can have various names like <gs_2n> <gs8> therefore OneLine-GUI couldn't
run correctly.

@{B}
NOTE 1: You can TRY to use OneLine GUI by changing the executable's
        name to <gs>.

NOTE 2: This change can make Ghostscript / OneLine quite unstable.
        The OneLine GUI is specific for Ghostscript 8.50.

        @{I}I suggest to install the version 8.50
@{UB}@{UI}

NOTE 3: note that GhostScript don't seems to handle white spaces in command line,
        even if included in '' or "".

        Es: "My File.pdf" isn't valid
            "My_File.pdf" is correct!


At the end of conversion, OneLine writes the Command Line of GhostScript
in the file "Ram:OL_GScript_CommandLine.log".



For specific informations about AFPL Ghostscript you can read the
original documentation included in the archives that you can download at:

   http://www.whoosh777.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/    * Amiga versione

   http://www.cs.wisc.edu/~ghost/                * Home page of Ghostscript
   http://www.ghostscript.com/
   http://www.pdflib.com/gsmanual
   http://www.volny.cz/rebus/ghostscript/
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_LOADSAVE "Load / save  prefs"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Load / Save  prefs@{UB}

This gadgets are used to Load and Save all the OneLine's preferences,
including the "Find/Repl" strings.

OneLine write them to "ENVARC:Oneline.prefs".
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_DEFAULT "Default prefs"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Default prefs@{UB}

This button will set the OneLine's default preferences:

On:                  |  Off:
---------------------------------------
OneLine              |  Find/Repl
Tabs                 |  Format
Seq                  |  AutoView
AutoSeq              |  Stats
Double               |  Save Res
MultiSpc             |  Delay
Leave Č              |  UseBreak
Chrs Errs            |  italiano
Std Seq              |  Ghostscript 8.50
UnPrint              |
Visual. = DEFAULT    |
colonne = 80         |
Tipo OS = AMIGA      |
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_TARGET "OS Target"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}OS Target@{UB}

With this cycle-gadget you can tell to OneLine the type of OS of
destination file: you can choose among "AMIGA", "MS_DOS", "MAC".

AMIGA
OneLine will write the character LF as line break

MS-DOS
OneLine will write the character's sequence CR+LF as line break

MAC
OneLine will write the character CR as line break
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_VIEW "View files"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}View files@{UB}

Here you can select the viewer to be used by OneLine to show the files.


You can set:

@{B}Default@{UB}
It's the OneLine's internal viewer and uses NList custom class.
* needs NList.mcc

@{B}Multiview@{UB}
It's the standard Amiga viewer.
Perhaps it's the best because uses the datatypes, and with the
datatypes you can show the images too.
It can be found in <SYS:Utilities/>: if <SYS:Utilities/> isn't in the path
type from Shell ""path SYS:Utilities/ add"

@{B}Editpad@{UB}
It's the standard editor for Amiga;
should be in <SYS:Tools/>

@{B}CygnusED@{UB}
It's a commercial text editor
should be in <C:>

@{B}>CON:@{UB}
With this option OneLine simply will redirect the output to >CON:
like the CLI command:

2.SYS:> type file >CON:

* This viewer needs only  "CON:"  device mounted  (!)


Generally, if OneLine don't show the file maybe don't find the viewer:
  1. check the path
  2. check if the file is in use or locked by another program
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_FILELUN "Number of columns"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Number of columns@{UB}

Here you can select the number of the columns to be used in @{"Format" link NODE_FORMAT} option.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_LIST "List of files"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}List of files@{UB}

Here you can see the files that OneLine will convert and their length.

You can order all files by clicking on the title of listview.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_ADD "Add files"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Add files@{UB}

With this button you can add some files to the list.
The file are automatically ordered.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_CLEAR "Clear list"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Clear list@{UB}

This button will clear all the list.
(don't delete the files from your HardDisk)
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_ERASE "Erase files"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Erase files@{UB}

With this option you can erase a single or specific file from the list.
(don't delete the files from your HardDisk)
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_COPY "Copy files"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Copy files@{UB}

This function copy the selected files in the location that you want.
A requester will be open to choose the destination directory.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_RENAME "Rename files"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Rename files@{UB}

This function will rename the selected files.
A requester will be open for each file.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_DELETE "Delete files"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Delete files@{UB}

This function will delete the selected files from your HardDisk and from the list:

@{B}WARNING! the files will be lost!@{UB}
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_PRINT "Print files"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Print files@{UB}

Simply send the file selected, to PRT: one char at a time,
about like  "type <filename> >PRT:"  from shell.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_GO "Start conversion"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Start conversion@{UB}

With this button you can start the conversion.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_LOCAL "Translation of OneLine 1.4"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Translation of OneLine 1.4@{UB}

OneLine 1.4 supports locale.library.

In the archive (OneLine14/catalogs/) you can find the files

  OneLine.cd
  OneLine.catalog (italian) v1.0
  OneLine.ct      (italian) v1.0


If you would translate OneLine to other languages you can upload the
translation's files on Aminet or send them to me: i'll include them in the
archive.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_BUGS "BUGS"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Bugs@{UB}

BUG: Sometimes the options aren't updated at the first pressure of buttons.


If you find a bug please send me an Email with the subject "OneLine bug",
your configuration and, if it's a conversion bug, the file with
the "text frame" that generate the bug.

About usage with GhostScript 8.50:
if you find a bug make sure if it's a bug of OneLine or one of GhostScript!


I tested this program on:
* A4000, CyberStormMKIII 060/50, 128Mb RAM, CVisionPPC, OS 3.9,
  HD9.1Gb ATLAS SCSI-UW, HD80Gb Maxtor IDE, HP LaserJet 1200,
  HP ScanJet II SCSI, Yamaha CDRW 16-10-40 SCSI, CD-ROM 48x


and:
* same A4000 but OS3.1

* Pegasos2 G4 1GHz, MOS 1.4

* WinME PIII celeron 500, WinUAE 0.9.91  with OS3.9
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_HIST "History"


@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}History@{UB}
1.4.4▀(1-Jan-2006)
      -fixed: bug during parsing of - / '

      -fixed: some crash with longer requester's strings

      -new: now OneLine leave the commas between digits and " after digit


1.4.3 (25-Mar-2005)
      -fixed some bugs in "Statistics" section

      -fixed: if you click on "Abort" OneLine at the next conversion
       Abort the conversion at first step

      -new: OneLine recognize the sequence of period like "previous_word... next_word"

      -change: the sequences typed by the user with AutoSeq=ON, are skipped by others
       checks, even if they are faulty

      -many minor bugs fixed

      -OneLine.guide: the character for single-char "Find/Replace" was $ not &
       the sequence is  $:0xx  where xx is ASCII_CODE


1.4.2 (27-Feb-2005)
      -Added support for partial convertion:
       now is possible to select the lines to convert

      -Change: the "SaveRes" option was removed and included in "Stats" option


1.4.1 (22-Feb-2005)
      -fixed some bugs in the installer script

      -fixed a bug in recognition of signs []

      -fixed a wrong lines counting

      -reworked the statistics section

      -minor fixes

      -changes in the .catalog .cd .ct


1.4   (14-Feb-2005)
      -switched to @{"MUI" link NODE_MUI} interface

      -added @{"locale" link NODE_LOCAL}.library support

      -added @{"GhostScript 8.50" link NODE_GHOST} support (beta)

      -added listview to support more than one file

      -added @{"Copy" link NODE_COPY}, @{"Rename" link NODE_RENAME}, @{"Delete" link NODE_DELETE} options
       to the listview

      -added @{"Find / Replace" link NODE_FINDREP} (thanks to MrCiccio), @{"Stats" link NODE_STATS}, @{"Select" link NODE_SELECT}, @{"Seq" link NODE_STRANGE},
       @{"Auto Seq" link NODE_AUTOSEQ}, @{"Std Seq" link NODE_STDSEQ}, @{"Italiano" link NODE_ITA} and @{"Unprint" link NODE_UNPRINT} options
       to file's conversion

      -added "Load" and "Save" prefs

      -added on-line help

      -fixed "Print" if the printer isn't connected OneLine wait forever

      -improved all existing conversion's fuctions

      -change: erased Input-Output gadgets.
       Now OneLine pick the file from the listview and save the converted
       file in the same directory but with the new extension (.OL for
       normal converted files and .OLF for those formatted with "Format"
       option.

      -change: included the logo in C source


1.3   (25-Mar-2002)
      -Totally rewritten, except some conversion's functions

      -Added a GUI (thanks to Jon Peterson)

      -Added '"', ']', ')' to the "Comma Option" (thanks to AntCer #)

      -Added "Save TO" Option to Save the Converted text with the
       specified number of columns

      -Added "Print" Option: only an easy print >PRT:

      -Added a "check & erase spaces" at line's begin
       (any new option: included in "Multiple-Spaces" option)

      -Removed [n] in "p[n]" option to set the lines between
       the paragraphs; the option "p" is present always

      -Improved the checking with the "e" & "c" options


(Only major changes)
1.2   -Added "-l" option to switch on/off the CR-LF erasing.
      -Added ".", ":", ";" checks to the "Comma Option" (-c)
      -Added "-p[n]" to leave the begin/end Paragraph codes,
       and  [n]  lines between the paragraphs    (thanks to D.Robb)
      -Added "e" option to find a possible type error

1.1   -Added Overwrite request
      -Added "Comma Optimize" option: erases the spaces before commas and add
       one space after (comma) if isn't;

1.0   First public release. (04-Jan-2002)
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_MUI "MUI"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}MUI - Magic User Interface@{UB}


                              Version 3.8

                  (c) Copyright 1992-97, Stefan Stuntz
                             - ShareWare -
------------------------------------------------------------------------

MUI  is  an object oriented system to create and maintain graphical user
interfaces.  From  a programmers point of view, using MUI saves a lot of
time  and  makes life much easier. Thinking about complicated terms like
window resizing or font sensitivity is simply not neccesary.

On  the  other hand, users of MUI based applications have the ability to
customize  nearly every pixel of a programs interface according to their
personal taste.

Please click on the Install-MUI icon to install MUI on your system or to
update from previous versions.  Latest news and support  can be found on
Internet at www.sasg.com.

                              ***********

                               Attention

    If you're still not registered for MUI, check the new and unique
  shareware lottery and great discounts at www.sasg.com. Give it a try!

-----------------------------------------------------------------------



